  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd2 \u0dad\u0dd0\u0db6\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dda \u0dbb\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dbb\u0dcf\u0da2\u0d9a\u0dd3\u0dba \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dba\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dcf\u0d9c \u0d9a\u0dc5 \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The house that Ranil had donated to Royal College was set on fire",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A group of saboteurs disguised as protesters set fire to the house of Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe, located at Fifth Lane, Colombo, where there were antiques.",
        "The Prime Minister has also issued a last will and testament donating this house to the Royal College of Colombo after him.",
        "Even though Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe is the person who held the office of Prime Minister the most number of times in the country, he never moved to the Colombo Temple Tree House, which was the official residence of the Prime Minister.",
        "Although he went to Temple Tree House for official work, he spent his life in this house. It is also said that some of the books in this house were available in Sri Lanka only in the library of that house.",
        "The Prime Minister as well as his wife Prof. Maithrie Wickramasinghe also spent her life in this house. This house was inherited by the Prime Minister and was built according to the old architecture."
      ],
